    <briefdescription>
<para>This block can be used to estimate the shift of a signal on input 1 in relation to another on input 2. For example the constant number of delay samples due to hardware effect from a signal source can be estimated. The calculation of the shift is done by a cross correlation of the input signals. The number of correlations in samples is given with num_xcorr. The output message is the number of delay samples with the identifier (symbol) &apos;sync_pulse&apos;. This can be displayed with the &apos;Print Results&apos; block. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>num_xcorr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Number of cross correlations </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
